Starbucks,1,"Di Bandung, Starbucks Store yang paling sering saya kunjungi adalah store di PVJ, Ciwalk dan 23 Paskal. Tiap ke 3 mall ini sudah pasti selalu ada 'break time' nongkrong di Starbucks, sehabis shopping, kuliner atau nonton bioskop. Belum store Starbucks yang di Jakarta (SenCi, Kokas, PIM, dan lain-lain). tetapi tidak tau kenapa, pelayanan di store Starbucks 23 Paskal ini adalah yang terburuk. Staffnya hampir semua judes dan sangat tidak ramah. Apalagi kalau saya mau order beverages pakai reward. Kebetulan rewards free beverages grande saya ada 25, belum lagi rewards yang lain seperti free add-on, 20% off venti, one for you one to share, buy 1 get 1 venti, 20% off any food, notebook & tumbler line, dan lain-lain. Aneh saja menurut saya, kalau customer yang memesan menggunakan rewards, lalu diperlakukan tidak ramah. Padahal program reward ini adalah program dari pihak Starbucks sendiri. Kita coba hitung2an ya. 1 star reward didapatkan customer setiap transaksi Rp5,000. untuk setiap 100 star customer mendapat 1 free reward, yang artinya setiap pembelanjaan Rp500,000. Bulan ini saja saya punya 34 Rewards. yang artinya saya sudah belanja 34 x Rp500,000 = Rp17,000,000 Hanya untuk mengambil 1 reward free beverages grande saja, sampai dijudesin sama kasirnya. Ada yang salah kayanya sama management store Starbucks di 23 Paskal Mall Bandung. Sampai2 staffnya semua pada tidak ramah begitu.",Negative,0,1,0,1,1;

title: Starbucks PVJ,2,"A Scorching Disappointment of Starbucks PVJ Outdoor This used to be my go-to spot for a relaxing and productive day out. The outdoor area was an oasis of calm and comfort, perfect for catching up with friends or getting some work done. However, everything changed for the worse when they decided to cut down the trees and remove the creeping plants that adorned the glass roof. What was once a cool and inviting space is now a sweltering sauna, especially during the day. Here's a breakdown of the current situation: Unbearable Heat: The removal of the trees and plants means there's absolutely no shade. The glass roof traps heat, making the outdoor area unbearably hot and stuffy. Deserted Space: It's no surprise that the outdoor area is now practically deserted during the day. No one wants to bake under the scorching sun while trying to enjoy their coffee. Service & Food Remain Unchanged: The service is still decent, although they do occasionally miss specific details in orders. The food remains decent as well. It's incredibly disappointing to see such a drastic change to what was once a fantastic space. The lack of shade has completely ruined the outdoor ambiance. I hope Starbucks PVJ reconsiders this change and finds a way to bring back the much-needed shade and greenery. Until then, I'll be taking my business elsewhere, at least during the daytime hours.",Negative,1,1,0,1,0;

title: Starbucks PVJ
text: Satu satunya pelayanan yang kurang mengenakan disini.
